'''Günter Bischof''' (born 6 October 1953 in [[Mellau]], [[Vorarlberg]]) is an [[Austria]]n-[[United States|American]] historian and university professor. A specialist in 20th century diplomatic history, and a graduate of [[University of New Orleans]], [[Innsbruck University]] and the [[Harvard University]], he currently serves as a Marshall Plan professor of history at the University of New Orleans.<ref name="uno">[http://history.uno.edu/faculty/bischof.cfm history.uno.edu]</ref>
