'''Raymond Culos''' (born April 18, 1936 in [[Vancouver]], [[British Columbia]]) is an author who has chronicled the history of  the [[Italy|Italian]] community in the [[Lower Mainland]] of [[British Columbia]]. Vancouver's Society of Italians,<ref name="Wood2004">{{cite book|last=Wood|first=Patricia K.|title=Nationalism from the Margins: Italians in Alberta and British Columbia|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=SDRjRtxSMzkC&pg=PA7|accessdate=25 September 2011|date=September 2004|publisher=McGill-Queen's Press - MQUP|isbn=978-0-7735-2370-8|pages=7–}}</ref> Volumes 1, 2 and 3 has preserved the history of this cultural group.

