'''Stephen Alford''' [[Fellow of the Royal Historical Society|FRHistS]] (born 1970) is a British historian and academic. He has been professor of early modern British history at the [[University of Leeds]] since 2012. Educated at the [[University of St Andrews]], he was formerly a [[British Academy]] Post-doctoral Research Fellow at the [[University of Cambridge]] (1997–99) and junior research fellow of [[Fitzwilliam College, Cambridge]] and, between 1999 and 2012, a fellow in history at [[King's College, Cambridge]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.leeds.ac.uk/arts/profile/20030/946/stephen_alford |title=Profile - Faculty of Arts - University of Leeds - Stephen Alford |publisher=Leeds.ac.uk |accessdate=2017-05-09}}</ref> He has been a fellow of the [[Royal Historical Society]] since 2000. He was taught by [[John Guy (historian)|John Guy]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.leeds.ac.uk/arts/profile/20030/946/stephen_alford |accessdate=2018-04-15}}</ref>

